The mean is the average of all numbers in a data set.   

$\begin{align}
\text{mean}& = \dfrac{\text{sum of numbers}}{\text{number of numbers}}\\\\
&=\dfrac{800\text{ years of service}}{40\text{ people}}\\\\
&=20\dfrac{\text{ years of service}}{\text{ person}}
\end{align}$

